laboratory_examinations.findings: 4+ (>10 per 1000X FIELD): POLYMORPHONUCLEAR LEUKOCYTES. NO MICROORGANISMS SEEN.

Mild bibasilar atelectasis, 4-mm pulmonary nodule in the left lower lobe (stable for almost ___ years). Tiny 4-mm hypodense lesion in the dome of the liver, likely a simple cyst or hemangioma. Normal gallbladder, pancreas, spleen, stomach, adrenal glands, kidneys, and small bowel loops. 14-mm extraluminal collection of predominantly air with some fluid adjacent to inflamed sigmoid colon.
